## Why This Is Asked

Tests understanding of stability and permutation-based sorting, ensuring candidates can separate data from its keys and reason about time/space trade-offs.

## Key Concepts

- Stable sort
- Permutations
- Time/space complexity
- Merge-based sorting on indices

## Code Example

```javascript
function stableSortIndicesByValue(A){
  const idx = Array.from({length: A.length}, (_, i) => i);
  function merge(left, right){
    const res = [];
    let i = 0, j = 0;
    while (i < left.length && j < right.length){
      if (A[left[i]] <= A[right[j]]) res.push(left[i++]);
      else res.push(right[j++]);
    }
    while (i < left.length) res.push(left[i++]);
    while (j < right.length) res.push(right[j++]);
    return res;
  }
  function sort(arr){
    if (arr.length <= 1) return arr;
    const m = Math.floor(arr.length / 2);
    const L = sort(arr.slice(0, m));
    const R = sort(arr.slice(m));
    return merge(L, R);
  }
  const P = sort(idx);
  return { P, sorted: P.map(i => A[i]) };
}
```

## Why This Is Asked

Tests ability to model DP with obstacles and variable step sizes, requiring careful base cases and transition logic. It also assesses both memoization and tabulation familiarity.

## Key Concepts

- DP with multiple transitions (1..k)
- Handling blocked steps
- Memoization vs tabulation
- Time complexity: O(n*maxJump); Space: O(n) (or O(maxJump) with optimization)

## Code Example

```javascript
// Bottom-up tabulation
function countWays(n, maxJump, blocked) {
  const dp = new Array(n + 1).fill(0);
  dp[0] = 1;
  for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    if (blocked[i]) { dp[i] = 0; continue; }
    for (let j = 1; j <= maxJump; j++) {
      if (i - j >= 0) dp[i] += dp[i - j];
    }
  }
  return dp[n];
}
```

```javascript
// Memoized recursive version
function countWaysRec(n, maxJump, blocked, i = n, memo = {}) {
  if (i === 0) return 1;
  if (i < 0 || blocked[i]) return 0;
  if (memo[i] !== undefined) return memo[i];
  let ways = 0;
  for (let t = 1; t <= maxJump; t++) ways += countWaysRec(n, maxJump, blocked, i - t, memo);
  memo[i] = ways;
  return ways;
}
```

